**_What is JSX?_**
JSX is a Javascript Extension Syntax used in React to easily write HTML(not pure HTML it's like html syntax) and Javascript together.
example -> const jsx = <h1>This is JSX</h1>
This is simple JSX code in React.

**_Superpowers of JSX_**
It simply makes code easy to write and understand,improve readability as well. It helps too in protecting our application from XSS attacks.

**_Role of type attribute in script tag? What options can i use there?_**
The type attribute specifies the type of the script. The type attribute identifies the content between the script tags.
OPTIONS are :
application/javascript
application/ecmascript
module

**_{TitleComponent} vs {TitleComponent/} vs {TitleComponent} vs {/TitleComponent} in JSX_**
{TitleComponent} - Value contained in TItleComponent can be rendered within curly braces by placing TitleComponent within it. {}

{<TitleComponent/>} - Specifies opening as well as closing tag of a component altogether. (Here it will render Title Component)

{<TitleComponent></TitleComponent>} - It specifies opening and closing tags of a component separately. (Here it will render Title Component).
